{"questionId":"9073481","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The diagram represents a diverging mirror being used to view an object.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/152662b98ea46b46385a5784a5ed28799930c290.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The image observed is virtual. Outline the meaning of virtual image.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">light rays do not pass through the image<br></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">do not form an image on a screen<br></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">appear to have come from a point<br></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">formed by extension of rays </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">✓</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle4\">OWTTE.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073481","referenceCode":"20N.3.SL.TZ0.10b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The image observed is virtual. Outline the meaning of virtual image.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (Core topics)","C.1 – Introduction to imaging","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}